# .dockerignore — ALLOW LIST for the Docker build context (`build: .`).
# `*` excludes everything (dotfiles included — Go glob, not shell glob);
# only the !re-includes below reach the Docker daemon. Any new file is
# excluded automatically, so nothing can leak into an image by default.
# To ship a new file: add a !line here AND a COPY line in the Dockerfile.
#
# Syntax is one pattern per line, same globbing as .gitignore:
#   name        matches a file/dir at the ROOT of the context only
#   !pattern    re-includes something excluded by an earlier line
#   !dir/**     needed to re-include a directory's contents (just !dir is not)

# Exclude everything by default
*

# Build inputs — exactly the files the Dockerfile COPYs
!nginx.conf
!index.html
!sw.js
!favicon.ico
!404.html
